text: Stigmella symmora is a moth of the family Nepticulidae. It is only known from the southern Gulf coast of South Australia. The wingspan is 5.2-5.7 mm for males and 5–6 mm for females. The larvae probably feed on Dodonaea viscosa. They mine the leaves of their host plant. ==External links== *Australian Faunal Directory *Australian Nepticulidae (Lepidoptera): Redescription of the named species Category:Nepticulidae Category:Moths of Australia
